Cricket South Africa’s interim board and its Members' Council look far from seeing eye-to-eye. They remain divided on the make-up of the new permanent board. CSA acting president, and Members' Council chair, Rihan Richards, has more on this. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The chair of the Cricket SA Members' Council, Rihan Richards says it's untrue that they do not want to implement the 2013 Nicholson Report recommendations. The Council and the Interim Board are at loggerheads over the independence of a new board. READ: CSA Members' Council reject call for independent directors Richardson says the CSA's current governing structure was agreed to by Sascoc, CSA and the sports ministry. Watch the full interview with Cricket SA Members' Council Chair, Rihan Richards in the video above.